sample_data.name: Linux by Zabbix agent
sample_data.description:
This is an official Linux template. It requires Zabbix agent 7.0 or newer.

Notes on filesystem (FS) discovery:
- The ext4/3/2 filesystem reserves space for privileged usage, typically set at 5% by default.
- BTRFS allocates a default of 10% of the volume for its own needs.
- To mitigate potential disasters, FS usage triggers are based on the maximum available space.
  - Utilization formula: 'pused = 100 - 100 * (available / total - free + available)'
- The FS utilization chart, derived from graph prototypes, reflects FS reserved space as the difference between used and available space from the total volume.

You can discuss this template or leave feedback on our forum https://www.zabbix.com/forum/zabbix-suggestions-and-feedback/387225-discussion-thread-for-official-zabbix-template-for-linux

Generated by official Zabbix template tool "Templator"

sample_queries.question: What is the system cpu util of Zabbix server?
natural_variations: system cpu util for Zabbix server
show system cpu util Zabbix server
sample_queries.sql:
SELECT ROUND(h.value, 2) as value
FROM history h
JOIN items i ON h.itemid = i.itemid
JOIN hosts hs ON i.hostid = hs.hostid
WHERE hs.host = 'Zabbix server' AND i.key_ LIKE 'system.cpu.util%'
ORDER BY h.clock DESC LIMIT 1;

sample_queries.question: How many active problems?
sample_queries.sql: SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM triggers WHERE value = 1 AND status = 0;

sample_queries.question: List all active problems
sample_queries.sql:
SELECT t.description, t.priority, h.host
FROM triggers t
JOIN functions f ON t.triggerid = f.triggerid
JOIN items i ON f.itemid = i.itemid
JOIN hosts h ON i.hostid = h.hostid
WHERE t.value = 1 AND t.status = 0
ORDER BY t.priority DESC;

sample_queries.question: Average CPU of Zabbix server in last 5 minutes
natural_variations: cpu average Zabbix server last 5 minutes
sample_queries.sql:
SELECT ROUND(AVG(h.value), 2) as avg_cpu
FROM history h
JOIN items i ON h.itemid = i.itemid
JOIN hosts hs ON i.hostid = hs.hostid
WHERE hs.host = 'Zabbix server' 
  AND i.key_ LIKE 'system.cpu.util%'
  AND h.clock > UNIX_TIMESTAMP(NOW() - INTERVAL 5 MINUTE);

sample_queries.question: Top 5 hosts by CPU usage
sample_queries.sql:
SELECT h.host, ROUND(AVG(hist.value), 2) as avg_cpu
FROM hosts h
JOIN items i ON h.hostid = i.hostid
JOIN history hist ON i.itemid = hist.itemid
WHERE i.key_ LIKE 'system.cpu.util%'
  AND hist.clock > UNIX_TIMESTAMP(NOW() - INTERVAL 5 MINUTE)
  AND h.status = 0
GROUP BY h.host
ORDER BY avg_cpu DESC
LIMIT 5;

latest_metric_value.description: Get latest value for a metric
latest_metric_value.sql_template:
SELECT ROUND(h.value, 2) as value, FROM_UNIXTIME(h.clock) as timestamp
FROM {history_table} h
JOIN items i ON h.itemid = i.itemid
JOIN hosts hs ON i.hostid = hs.hostid
WHERE hs.host = '{host}' AND i.key_ = '{item_key}'
ORDER BY h.clock DESC LIMIT 1;

average_metric_time_range.description: Get average metric value over time range
average_metric_time_range.sql_template:
SELECT ROUND(AVG(h.value), 2) as avg_value
FROM {history_table} h
JOIN items i ON h.itemid = i.itemid
JOIN hosts hs ON i.hostid = hs.hostid
WHERE hs.host = '{host}' 
  AND i.key_ = '{item_key}'
  AND h.clock > UNIX_TIMESTAMP(NOW() - INTERVAL {minutes} MINUTE);

active_problems.sql:
SELECT 
    t.description,
    t.priority,
    h.host,
    FROM_UNIXTIME(e.clock) as problem_time
FROM triggers t
JOIN functions f ON t.triggerid = f.triggerid
JOIN items i ON f.itemid = i.itemid
JOIN hosts h ON i.hostid = h.hostid
LEFT JOIN events e ON t.triggerid = e.objectid AND e.source = 0 AND e.object = 0
WHERE t.value = 1 AND t.status = 0
ORDER BY t.priority DESC;

host_metrics_summary.description: Get all latest metrics for a host
host_metrics_summary.sql_template:
SELECT 
    i.name,
    i.key_,
    h.value,
    FROM_UNIXTIME(h.clock) as last_update
FROM items i
JOIN (
    SELECT itemid, value, clock
    FROM history
    WHERE itemid IN (SELECT itemid FROM items WHERE hostid = (SELECT hostid FROM hosts WHERE host = '{host}'))
    UNION ALL
    SELECT itemid, value, clock
    FROM history_uint
    WHERE itemid IN (SELECT itemid FROM items WHERE hostid = (SELECT hostid FROM hosts WHERE host = '{host}'))
) h ON i.itemid = h.itemid
WHERE i.status = 0
ORDER BY h.clock DESC;

index_recommendations: Ensure clock column is indexed in history tables
Composite index on (itemid, clock) for history queries
Index on hostid in items table
Index on key_ in items for metric lookups

collection_flow.3_value_storage: Actual values go to history/history_uint/etc based on value_type
collection_flow.4_aggregation: Data aggregated into trends tables for long-term storage

query_flow.latest_value: hosts -> items -> history (ORDER BY clock DESC LIMIT 1)
query_flow.average_value: hosts -> items -> trends (AVG over time range)

hints: Always filter history tables by clock to use time-based indexes
Use LIMIT to restrict result sets, especially in history queries
For time ranges > 1 hour, query trends instead of history
Avoid SELECT * - specify only needed columns
Use composite indexes on (itemid, clock) for history queries
Always join on indexed columns (hostid, itemid, triggerid)
Filter as early as possible in the join chain
Use INNER JOIN instead of LEFT JOIN when possible
Limit the number of joins to 4-5 for optimal performance
For latest value: ORDER BY clock DESC LIMIT 1
For averages: Use AVG() with clock filter
For counts: Use COUNT(*) with appropriate WHERE clause
Cache frequently accessed data in application layer
Recent data: clock > UNIX_TIMESTAMP(NOW() - INTERVAL X)
